Peter Obi, the candidate of the Labour Party (LP), is leading in the presidential election in Plateau state. Obi has won eight of the 10 LGAs announced so far, while Atiku Abubakar of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) has won two. Meanwhile, Bola Tinubu of the All Progressives Congress (APC) is yet to win any. There are seven more LGAs to be announced. In Kwara, Tinubu has been declared the winner of the state by the returning officer of the Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC). He polled 263,572 votes to defeat Atiku who secured 136,909. Meanwhile, Peter Obi polled 31,166 votes. The registered number of voters in the state is 1,695,927 while 497,519 were accredited. Tinubu was also declared the winner of the presidential election in Oyo state, polling 449,884 votes to defeat Atiku who had 182,977 and Obi who secured 99,110. There are 3,237,310 registered voters in Oyo while 854,439 were accredited to vote. Atiku Abubakar however won the election in Osun state, polling 354,365 votes to edge Tinubu who had 343,945. Obi secured 23,283 votes in the state while Rabiu Kwankwaso of the New Nigeria Peoples Party (NNPP) polled 713. There are a total of 1,954,800 registered voters in Oyo while 759,300 were accredited to vote.